===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
[[File:Lewes Bonfire, fox figures cropped.jpg|200px|thumb|Image depicting the protoform of зҶ’.]]
{{liushu|p}} вҖ“ The protoform is [[рӨҮҫ]]. рӨҮҫ is a pictogram of two intersecting torches, meaning the fire light. In Qin and Han, the crossing of the torches "д№Ӯ" became "еҶӮ", and "рӨҮҫ" is no longer used as independent character as a third "зҒ«" (fire) was added into "рӨҮҫ". Thus, "зҶ’" was formed.

===Etymology===
{{och-l|зҶ’|tr=wГӘЕӢ}} belongs to a word-family whose stem is *''weЕӢ'' "bright, dazzle", which converges with {{och-l|зһ¬|tr=*win}} "to move the eyes" ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Other items in the same word-family are:

* {{och-l|зң©|tr=wГ®n(s)?|troubled sight, deluded, deceive}},
* {{och-l|зӮ«|tr=wГ®ns|bright, dazzle, show off}},
* {{och-l|з‘©|tr=wreЕӢ|bright, color of jade > kind of gem}}
* {{och-l|зҶІ|tr=kwГӘЕӢК”|light, flame, blaze}}, which is {{och-l|зҶ’|tr=wГӘЕӢ}} with *''k-'' nominalizer.
* {{och-l|жҰ®|tr=wreЕӢ|flower > flowering, prosperity > glory}}, which is the same word as {{och-l|зҶ’|tr=wГӘЕӢ}}.

This word-family could be {{inh|zh|sit-pro|-}} and related to {{cog|lus|ven}} & {{m|lus|veng||to be open; to be unobstructed by trees, clouds, etc; to be clear; to be free of clouds; to be bright (as weather)}} (ibid.).

